olive oil
1 packet Mac & Cheese with Ham
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 punnet cherry tomatoes
1 bottle Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing

• Preheat oven to 180°C/160°C fan-forced.
• Remove plastic film from mac & cheese tray.
• Place tray directly on wire oven rack and bake until piping hot, 28-30 minutes.
Remove from oven, then let stand for 1 minute.

• Meanwhile, halve cherry tomatoes.
• In a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, cherry tomatoes and balsamic &
olive oil dressing.

• Divide mac and cheese and cherry tomato salad between bowls. Enjoy!